Grandmaster Suk Ku Kim is a martial arts martial artist from South Korea who founded the Tae Kuk Mu Sul combat system.  His distinctive style represents a blending of traditional Korean fighting techniques.  Tae Kuk Mu Sul encompasses striking, grappling, acrobatics, pressure point manipulation, weaponsuse, and more.  Kim himself is a ninth degree black belt. In the past, he has trained Korean soldiers and police officers in the art of handtohand combat. He now lives in the Sacramento area and currently teaches Tae Kuk Mu Sul at the ARC Martial Arts Room at UC Davis.
